                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.7962/10–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>, Political Adviser to
                        the Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater, at Caserta</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 16, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>899. Urtel 3799, Oct 5.<note n="82" xml:id="d1214fn1">Not printed.</note> Civil
                    Aviation Section War Dept was unable to act on Rome airport and matter was
                    referred to Air Coordinating Board. No decision has been reached by latter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
